reported%20that%20there%20weren't%20any%20signs%20that%20the%20IRS%20initially%20pushed%20back%20against%20Trump's%20first%20claim%2C%20which%20surprised%20tax%20experts%20who%20spoke%20with%20the%20outlets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20tax%20advisors%20in%202010%20tried%20to%20obtain%20additional%20benefits%20from%20the%20skyscraper%20project%20by%20transitioning%20the%20company%20that%20owned%20the%20building%20into%20a%20new%20partnership.%20But%20Trump%20wielded%20the%20levers%20of%20power%20for%20both%20companies.%20And%20for%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20he%20used%20the%20business%20move%20to%20try%20to%20claim%20%24168%20million%20in%20new%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20Trump's%20claims%2C%20the%20IRS%20conducted%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh-level%20legal%20review%26quot%3B%20before%20they%20began%20their%20inquiry%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20looking%20at%20the%20inquiry%2C%20The%20Times%20and%20ProPublica%20%E2%80%94%20and%20tax%20experts%20%E2%80%94%20concluded%20that%20the%20revision%20pursued%20by%20the%20IRS%20would%20give%20Trump%20an%20updated%20tax%20bill%20exceeding%20%24100%20million%2C%20excluding%20any%20additional%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Trump%2C%20the%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20Trump%20Organization%2C%20responded%20to%20the%20report%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20company%20was%20%26quot%3Bconfident%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20actions%20regarding%20the%20Chicago%20skyscraper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20matter%20was%20settled%20years%20ago%2C%20only%20to%20be%20brought%20back%20to%20life%20once%20my%20father%20ran%20for%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20Times%20and%20ProPublica.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20confident%20in%20our%20position%2C%20which%20is%20supported%20by%20opinion%20letters%20from%20various%20tax%20experts%2C%20including%20the%20former%20general%20counsel%20of%20the%20IRS.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20